labels.label:
The Jolt mapping in the processor to the right
adds one hard-coded key/value pair to each
element in the incoming JSON array
-
[
  {
    "operation": "default",
    "spec": {
      "cat[]": {
        "*": {
          "insert-data-here": "some extra data"
        }
      }
    }
  }
]
-
Explanation: The "default" spec is used to add 
hard-coded values to the JSON data
-
1. "cat[]" states to look for the array which has
>> the key name of "cat"
2. "*" states to do upcoming statements to 
>> every element in the previously-mentioned
>> array ("cat")
3.  "insert-data-here": "some extra data"
>> will insert  "insert-data-here": "some extra data"
>> as a key/value pair within the JSON data

